WEBVTT

1
00:00:03.600 --> 00:00:16.008
There are exactly two settings on this dashboard that
change everything else. Set them once, and every chart,
every table, every recommendation recomputes around them.
This is the one rule the whole machine runs on.

2
00:00:16.608 --> 00:00:35.448
The first is Min Cashflow. In plain English, it's your
profit target, the move in your favor you'd be happy to
bank as a win. The rule is dead simple. A trade counts as
a win the moment its MFE, its best favorable move, reaches
this number. Set it here, and it instantly defines what a
winner even is across your entire history.

3
00:00:36.048 --> 00:00:53.928
The second setting is Max MAE. That is your stop. And it
works in one direction only. It never cancels a win. If a
trade already reached your target, it stays a win, period.
It only protects your losers. A losing trade can never
cost you more than this. Set it to zero, and you're
trading with no stop at all.

4
00:00:54.528 --> 00:01:08.376
Then there's Attempts per Day, a lens for setups you take
more than once in a session. Count them all, just the
first, the first few, or only the second attempt. It never
deletes a single trade. It just changes which ones the
math is looking at right now.

5
00:01:08.976 --> 00:01:31.392
Now here's why this matters so much. These aren't just
inputs. They are the single source of truth. Change your
target or your stop, and watch. The win rate, the strike
rates, the expected values, the prop simulator, every
recommendation, all of it recomputes at once, off this one
rule. Nothing on the dashboard can ever disagree with
anything else, because everything reads from right here.

6
00:01:31.992 --> 00:01:47.376
So before you read another number anywhere on this screen,
set these two honestly, to the way you actually trade.
Your real target, your real stop. Get them right, and
everything downstream is the truth about your edge. Get
them wrong, and you're studying a strategy you don't even
trade.

7
00:01:47.976 --> 00:01:51.720
One target. One stop. And the entire dashboard obeys.
